accessibility.text: Aim: How can we run python programs directly from the shell?
Aim: How can we run python programs directly from the shell?
Make sure the file is executable (set correct file permissions).
In linux and linux-like systems, file permissions are used to determine what kinds of actions you can perform on a file.
The contents of the file can be viewed.
The contents of the file can be modified.
The file can be run on it’s own as a program
Each permission is independent of the others, so a file could have read permissions but not write, or could have execute permissions but not read…
